data.text:
Place to stay in Wykoff

4.91 out of 5 average rating, 373 reviews4.91 (373)

Historic Wykoff Jail Haus

Come explore the Historic Wykoff Jail Haus. The Jail Haus was built the late 1800’s and is owned by the city of Wykoff. Bike trails, trout fishing, Forestville State park, and cave exploration. There is kayaking and tubing 10 minutes away. Open over the winter months for snowmobiling, snowshoeing, cross country skiing, hunting and other winter activities. Playgrounds, restaurants, convenience / gas station all within walking distance. Located 40 miles south of Rochester in a town of 450 people.

Guest suite in Faribault

4.96 out of 5 average rating, 297 reviews4.96 (297)

Sherry's Suite

Our beautiful suite of private rooms will accommodate up to 4 people. You can expect a very private, peaceful and comfortable atmosphere. A place that you can call 'Home' while being away from yours. During this time, with the Coronavirus and the need for social distancing, Lisa & I would like to assure you that the Suite is completely yours and there is no shared space within the home. We take extra care in making sure you are in a safe, clean environment. Have safe travel's and stay healthy.

Guesthouse in Cannon Falls

4.99 out of 5 average rating, 212 reviews4.99 (212)

Cannon Valley Lucky Day Farm - Farmhouse Loft

A beautiful farmhouse loft just minutes from Cannon Falls and Red Wing! * Canoe, kayak or tube the Cannon River at Welch Mill -5 mi * Bicycle the 19.2-mile paved Cannon Valley Trail, trail crosses the property * Treasure Island Resort & Casino -11 mi * Hike Barn Bluff in Red Wing -13 mi * Golf at area courses * Wineries & breweries -4 mi * Drive the scenic Great River Road * Birdwatch eagles, grosbeaks, woodpeckers, and hummingbirds. * MOA and Twin Cities - 30 mi * Ski at Welch Village -6 mi

Barn in Stockholm

4.98 out of 5 average rating, 407 reviews4.98 (407)

Maiden Rock Barn (Pine Creek Rustic Road)

The Maiden Rock Barn is an ideal place to gather with friends, family or to spend some time alone. Located in the beautiful countryside of Maiden Rock township, WI, at the top of Pine Creek Rustic Road known for it's great birding and trout stream. Maiden Rock Barn is a few miles from the Mississippi River/Lake Pepin. The Barn is a short drive from the river towns of Maiden Rock(5 mi), Stockholm(7 mi), Pepin(11 mi) and near the birthsite of L. I. Wilder; (20 miles) from Red Wing or Wabasha.

Home in Kasson

4.96 out of 5 average rating, 101 reviews4.96 (101)

Home Sweet Minnesota

A few days or a few weeks away from home? Let us provide a comfortable and cozy get away in this turn of the century, two story home. Located in a quiet neighborhood with off-street parking, this property boasts large rooms, original hardwood floors and woodwork, a full kitchen, and laundry. The large, fenced in backyard, complete with playground and sandbox, makes this a child friendly space. The front porch and back patio provide outdoor room to grill, picnic, or just relax in a lawn chair.

Farm stay in Spring Valley

4.82 out of 5 average rating, 127 reviews4.82 (127)

Romantic Garden Retreat @ Whispering Winds

Steps from a stocked trout stream, this studio style, camping made easy, personal retreat is charming and comfortable. What could be better than sitting in a comfortable chair, reading a good book & sipping a glass of wine...or a cup of coffee/tea...or a pint from the local brewery...listening to the bird song? The firefly show has been spectacular, and the flowers are coming into full bloom! Whispering Winds Holistic Retreat is a conduit for healing your soul through nature and creativity.

Tiny home in Plainview

4.97 out of 5 average rating, 105 reviews4.97 (105)

Quaint 1 bedroom cabin, with amazing views!

Peaceful 1 bedroom cabin overlooking views of the beautiful whitewater valley (35 minutes away from Rochester Minnesota). Perfect for a quiet, off-the-grid, retreat. - compost toilet -two burner stove -gas heater for the colder months -5 gallons of water included, more If needed Queen size bed beneath 3ft by 3ft skylight with stunning views of stars at night. 120 private acres connected on two sides by the (WMA). 1 + mile of personal private hiking trails with scenic views.

Home in Stewartville

4.95 out of 5 average rating, 147 reviews4.95 (147)

"Walden Pond" Adventure Amidst 44 Private Acres

Embark on your own "Walden Pond" adventure and be at one with nature. Each season brings its own magic: the fiery colors in fall, crunching through snow in the winter, new life in spring, and sports and activities in the summer! The 2000 s.f. log home known as 'The Bungalow" offers romantic fireplace, 2 bedrooms, 2 baths, office/bedroom + huge entertainment room. Easy drive from Rochester and all roads clear in winter. Feel safe from current coronavirus . See more info below.

Home in Rochester

4.97 out of 5 average rating, 139 reviews4.97 (139)

Spacious Modern Home Near Mayo, St. Mary's Campus

- 5 min walk to Mayo Clinic, St. Mary’s campus - 3 bedrooms, 3 bathrooms, and a loft - unique design with vaulted ceiling and skylights in the style of Frank Lloyd Wright, one of its kind in the whole neighborhood - two-car garage + another dedicated parking space outside - walkable and safe family-friendly neighborhood close to downtown and all amenities - outside front and back patios - fusball play table - dedicated workspace - high speed wifi - Apple TVs - washer and dryer

Tiny home in Nerstrand

4.98 out of 5 average rating, 153 reviews4.98 (153)

The Tiny House at Trout Lily Farm

Trout Lily Farm is a beautiful, peaceful six acre hobby farm. The Tiny has its own semi-private area by apple trees and a scenic barn, with its own patio table/chairs, barbecue, and firepit. This 168 square foot one-level Tiny is suitable for 1-2 guests (one queen bed). Running purified water, electrical/propane stainless appliances, full tub/shower, composting toilet, internet. Fully furnished, with dishes, coffee maker and electric kettle, linens and toiletries.

Guesthouse in Pepin

4.99 out of 5 average rating, 157 reviews4.99 (157)

Rustic Modern Loft - Across from Winery/Lake View

Welcome to Pepin Guest Haus! Our cozy yet modern and fresh loft has beautiful views of Lake Pepin and is walking distance to everything in town - Villa Bellezza Winery, Pepin Marina, Harbor View Cafe, The Pickle Factory, Pepin Bistro, Laura Ingalls Wilder Museum, gift shops, etc. Pepin, Wisconsin is the hidden gem of the Midwest. As your hosts, we aim to share this treasure with you. Pepin Guest Haus is nicely appointed with everything you need for a relaxing trip!

Farm stay in Hayward

4.84 out of 5 average rating, 274 reviews4.84 (274)

Nordic Horse isolated farm stay for your family

COVID PROTOCOLS: Host follows Airbnb Cleaning Checklist between guests The Nordic Horse is a farm stay! This is a working horse farm, many of the horses are located on this property. Have coffee on deck overlooking a pasture with the two miniature (little ones can sit on them) ponies and the friendly llama that begs for carrots. The pigmy goats love to eat weeds you feed them. The house and barn were built in 1880 by Norwegian immigrants Ole and Britta.
